<p>Erin cut him off with a quiet whine, her tail bristled from base to tip and swishing against the back of the seat. “A! Come <em>on</em>!”</p>
<p>The cat’s grin turned to a laugh. “What do you mean, ‘come on’? You’d love it, you said so. You’d love to be a Centerpiece and come away with motherhood, I know you would! And you know I’m game, too.”</p>
