<p>Erin’s silence and Aaron’s grin lasted the next few minutes until they parked at the curb before a squat, suburban ranch house.</p>
<p>Aaron turned off the car and tugged up the parking break, leaning over to kiss his wife on the cheek, “Sorry if that was too far, E.”</p>
<p>When she didn’t respond, the cat reached for Erin’s paw, twining fingers with her. She smiled bashfully to him.</p>
<p>“No, was just thinking,” she murmured. “I <em>would</em> love that.”</p>
